            "id": "4618030",
            "title": "Novo files injunction to block Lilly’s weight-loss drug ads",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Novo Nordisk (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVO\" title=\"Novo Nordisk A/S\">NVO</a>) on Friday said it filed a preliminary injunction to immediately block Eli Lilly (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LLY\" title=\"Eli Lilly and Company\">LLY</a></span>) from running obesity and diabetes drug advertisements in the U.S.</p>\n<p>The filing in a federal court in the District of New Jersey came days after the company sued its U.S. rival, alleging that Lilly's advertising campaign for GLP-1 products misled American consumers.</p>\n<p>Novo (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVO\" title=\"Novo Nordisk A/S\">NVO</a>) on Tuesday announced the lawsuit, which alleged that the Indiana-based drugmaker engaged in false advertising by claiming its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4615863-novo-nordisk-sues-eli-lilly-glp-1-ads\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">GLP-1 treatments were superior.</a></p>\n<p>At the time, the company said it would file a preliminary injunction against Lilly (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LLY\" title=\"Eli Lilly and Company\">LLY</a>) if the Zepbound maker does not voluntarily remove the disputed ads. Lilly (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LLY\" title=\"Eli Lilly and Company\">LLY</a>) stood by the advertisements, noting that it will “vigorously defend” against Novo’s (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVO\" title=\"Novo Nordisk A/S\">NVO</a>) claims.</p>\n<p>\"Novo Nordisk is seeking a court order on ‌an <span>⁠</span>expedited basis to ensure people can access the accurate, complete picture of the treatments available to them today,<span>”</span> the Danish drugmaker said.</p>\n<p>The lawsuit filed in U.S. District Court ‌in New Jersey alleged that Lilly violated federal and state laws through its nationwide advertising campaigns for its GLP-1 drugs Mounjaro and Zepbound.</p>\n<p>Novo (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVO\" title=\"Novo Nordisk A/S\">NVO</a>) claimed that the commercials were misleading as they compared the highest doses of Lilly’s products with lower doses of its competing GLP-1s, Ozempic and Wegovy, while omitting a new higher-dose version that it said generates higher weight loss.</p>\n<p>Lilly (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LLY\" title=\"Eli Lilly and Company\">LLY</a>) didn’t immediately respond to a request for comment on Novo’s (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVO\" title=\"Novo Nordisk A/S\">NVO</a>) injunction.</p>\n\n</body></html>",
