            "id": "4618009",
            "title": "Bank of America raises dividend by 14% to $0.32/share",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Bank of America (BAC) declares <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20594449-bank-of-america-increases-common-stock-dividend-14-percent-to-0_32-per-share\">$0.32/share quarterly dividend</a>, <font color=\"green\">14.3% increase</font> from prior dividend of $0.28.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BAC/dividends/yield?source=news_bullet\">Forward yield</a> 2.09%</li>\n<li>Payable Sept. 25; for shareholders of record Sept. 4; ex-div Sept. 4.</li>\n<li>The company also continues to repurchase common stock under a $40B authorization from the board, which has been in effect since August 1, 2025.</li>\n<li>In the first half of 2026, the company repurchased $13.2B of common stock and paid $4B in dividends.</li>\n<li>As of June 30, 2026, the current share repurchase program had approximately $17B in common stock repurchases remaining.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BAC/dividends?source=news_bullet\">See BAC Dividend Scorecard, Yield Chart, &amp; Dividend Growth.</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n</body></html>",
